\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Oh yes, she could tell you - she could tell you a few nice stories. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Were there any newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Aye, the - of course then it was a case of - there were only halfpenny papers and - the North Star and - t
he paper that me father used to get - oh what was it they called that book, the paper me father used to get? Oh dear. I've forgot now. But a very very old one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Was it a magazine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Aye, a weekly. Of course he was - he was very - he was a bit keen 
on - the Parliament, a bit - bit keen on who was in and who wasn't in and - he was in - he was interested in Politics. Aye. Aye. I forget what they call that book now. But anyhow he - there was some - there was some - oh all old stories that used to - you
 know, poetry and so forth that he used to get interested in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 And you had Robby Burns because your mother was Scottish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Yes. Well I have Robbie Burns. I still have him, the one that me mother had. Aye. I've still got that. And - it was given - it
 was given to my mother by a dying man. This chap - he worked at the quarry. That morning there was an accident. The shot off, they were blasting. And the shot went off a little bit sooner than they'd anticipated. And it blew his right hand - in here, in 
his side. They brought him down from the clay and - mother, of course she was - she was - she was a good old nurse and - they were friendly and she went to see him and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4421866\charrsid2896712 so forth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 . And - before he died he said, mother - to my mother he said, Jane, he says, the
re'd Bobby Burns on drawer's top there. He says, it's yours. He says, get it. He says, I give it to you. And I have the very book in -
