no. But I can tell you - something - me father - was one of men - that introduced - the section of the N.U.R. to Standhope and they were threatened with the sack, if they didn't - stop this - introduction of a union. They didn't want it. They didn't want 
it in Stanhope. But I know - and - and they used to hold meetings, the usual meetings - occasionally in our house, and - four or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4421866\charrsid2896712 five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712  chaps used - and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4421866\charrsid2896712 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712  these little meetings, but the result was you know - that they that they got a - a section, they got e
nough what they made members - and they were connected with - Shildon. And my father was Secretary at Stanhope.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Of the union?
