n races and - that sort of thing. We used to make slings and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 What did you do with those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Well - you used to - try to throw a stone from your sling - right from the terrace across the railway, across the river, into the plantation at the bottom of the road that took you to the quarry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Did you ever throw that far?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Yes. Oh yes. Used to go that far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Were you an expert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Well - I was as good as the rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Did you ever play with your brother and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Well they used 
to consider themselves too - too old to play with us, unless - mind - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 You were quite a bit younger then them all weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Aye. Unless there - there was quite a number of them used to come always out. The weather was fine, a nice night,
 they got the skipping rope, a long one, well it was the clothes line or something of that or a rope of that description, and they used to skip and jump. And - of course - they used to - some of them - take sides, you see. Them that was out first and last
, aye, they used to work it up and they used to take sides. So many lads and so many lasses on each side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 And then you all played together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Oh aye, together then, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 On the back street. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Did you ever play in the yard or garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 No, they can't - oh they weren't large enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Did you ever play in anybody else's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Aye, especially if they got a new game of some sort and then we used to go and - and try it out. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Did you play anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Aye, down at the riverside. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
You played slings and skipping rope, what other games can you remember playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Well, we had a - we had a game we used to call - blobby, I know - aye. B - Blobby. Blobby. And you used to - make a 
hole, just a little hole about - as far round as a - as an egg, the long, as far round as an egg and about - half a cup deep. They used to make a line a certain distance from the hole where you used to stand. And you had - now, maybe there was - three or 
f
our of you playing. Now then you had - marbles. Now if - if one of the lads was a bit short - we - you used to say toe on. Well that meant that whoever was playing gave the thrower two marbles. And he - he put two in himself you see. And he used to stand 
a
t this - this mark and - try to get as many marbles as you could - into that little hole. And - as many marbles as you place in there they were yours when you took them out, if you got one in you got one in, if you got none in why - then it was the next l
ad to come on and try. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11363695 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 Any other games you remember that you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10187699 RT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
Yes. Penky off. Penky. Off. Well - you used to make a ring about - a foot across. Well a foot wide, a circle. Now then - you placed two, three or four, it all depends upon 
how many - was playing the games. And you put your marbles - in this ring. And there you are so many yards back. Made your line, and you had a penky, a metal one - very often. In fact ours was all metal. And you used to throw your metal penky to get as ma
n
y marbles out of that ring as you possibly could. You see. If the - sometimes you could work it - that - you - your penky would hit one - and it would cannon another one, and there was always a possibility of getting two out of that ring you see. And you 
u
sually - used to do that until the ring was empty. And then we played tip-cat. Well - well now. Tip-cat. You got a piece of wood about - oh anywhere from about six - you could have a foot long, but about - we used to play with them about six inches. And a
n
 inch square. And you tapered - now then, that - was a square piece of wood, you taped the ends but not quite to a point. It was - it - both - just - in a V shape really and - and you tapered it, of course - your point was round. Now, you had a - a stick,
 
maybe a couple of foot long - maybe four of you or six of you would play this game, two or three a side. Now, whoever went in first there was a - there was a ring, about same as the marble, a foot or - or eighteen inches and the bowler used to take this t
i
p - tip-cat and the tip-cat was marked one, two, three, and across. Now - when he bowled that to you you had to hit it if possible and send it as far as you possibly could, but any - anybody caught it - you were out. Yes. Yes. If anybody caught it you wer
e out. But you used to try and ra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4421866\charrsid2896712 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
 it as far as every you could. Of course they used to try all ways to stop it with the exception - of taking your jackets off and holding your jackets up for stop it that way. Aye. And - you're free to do anything as long as you stopped it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4421866\charrsid2896712 A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10627816\charrsid2896712 
nd - whatever number was - turned up on the tip-cat - one, two, three - but if it came X you were out. You were out. Just as it landed. Now - you see, it would maybe land pretty near on the ring you know and you wanted it away from that 
ring because you wanted to what we called chalk, if you didn't chalk you know it was - it was no use, you wanted a chalk, you - one was all right, as long as you chalked. Now then, you used to - this stick that you had in your hand - you used to try to hi
t
 the - the point, and that made the tip-cat jump - it jumped up and then you could - have a swing at it and knock it as far as maybe - well - you've oftener miss it than hit it and - wherever it went to you used to - count, if you could, as far as you cou
ld, the length of the stick from the tip-cat to you, you might get six. Might get six lengths. But if you got a good swish at it well you - you were all right. Aye.
