 mind getting them out and - there was a little bit of objection but not - not a lot but eventually they were got out of the window and they were just my fit, and - I had occasion to - to see the cobbler, and says, by he says, them's a pair of grand shoes
.
 He said, they're pigskin. I said, aye. Now he said, I'll tell you what, he says, I don't know who does the jobs for you, but he says, when you get these shoes soled, he says, whoever does them wants to sew them on. Stitch the soles on. He says, they'll m
a
ke a pair of brand new shoes. Just one raised that just went over the top, you know. Well, I said, I'll tell you what, I says, if all goes well, and I says, I want them repaired you can have the job. And I was as good as me word, I took the shoes down to 
